    "@agicash/opensecret": "1.0.0-rc.0 dropped the react peer-dep — the SDK is now framework-free with no tracked exception. Token storage is pluggable via configure({ storage }); the web passes the browserStorage helper and a headless host (Node/MCP) passes its own. auth.ts reads tokens through the configured provider (getConfig().storage.persistent), not window, and awaits getItem so sync (browser) and async (keychain/file/remote) stores both work."
